 &quot;He's safe, let him be,&quot; she calls out. After a few minutes of frowns and mutters they let him go and fade back to their posts. She looks Theseus over and shrugs, &quot;Come on I'm going to make tea and you can help me check out the huts, see which have survived,&quot; she points to where they are and starts to walk back, turns around for a moment, then makes her way back to Celaneo, and sits down with an &quot;umhp&quot;. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=theseusofthemiscrya>Theseus of Themiscrya</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Bronze Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 101<br> <font color=#993300>(6/4/03 9:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=50.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/ixltheseuslxl/myhomepage/theseus1.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Coming Home</span><hr size=1> Theseus was grateful that Lalita had spoken up for him.  He moved slowly, following her to the hut she had occupied with Celaneo.  He smiled a little nervously, &quot;Hey, Celaneo.  I um, came to help where I could.&quot;  He looked around the hut, &quot;I'll go head and start repairs to this hut and then move to the next one.&quot;  He was already laying his things in the corner planning what he was going to need to make the repairs.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=battlingangel>Battling Angel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Bronze Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 110<br> <font color=#993300>(6/4/03 11:41 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFr