ollecting the needed materials to begin repair of the huts in the village.  He had already set up a small shop area and secured some tools that he'd found in one of the storage huts around the village.  He was able to move around without too much grief or worry for the time being and he was content to simply be doing something with his hands that enabled him to keep his mind on other things.  <br>
<br>
While it was cooler to work without his shirt on, the sun bore down on his bare skin, leaving it a slight reddened color.  He paid it no mind and continued to work, moving to install the reinforcements to the hut and ensure that not only was it stable but it was also flexible lest a strong wind come through.  He had noticed Kalasin when she had approached Lalita and Celaneo, but he had been too distracted by his work to interfere and he was also keen enough to know that it was not his place to greet visitors to the village. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <br><font color=#993300>- </font><a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite>Amazons Unite</a><font color=#993300> - </font><a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm4>Sisterhood of the Crimson Stone</a> <font color=#993300> - </font><a href="http://pub163.ezboard.com/bmythicalodysseyforum">Home</a><font color=#993300> - </font><br><br><br><br>Powered By <a href=http://www.ezboard.com/>ezboard®</a> Ver. 7.3m<br>Copyright ©1999-2003 ezboard, Inc.</center></body></html>  

